<image 1>(asthma) fill in the blank for the pathophysiology pathway (D.C= dendritic cell)

A. Columnar epithelial cells detect activated Dendritic cells and secrete thymic stromal lymphocytes.
B. Activated Dendritic cell secretes a hormone.
C. Mast cell is activated through the activation of the D.C and secretes thymic stromal lymphocytes.
D. Thymic stromal lymphocytes are created by TH2 cells which have detected the activation of the dendritic cell.

The correct answer to fill in the blank for the pathophysiology pathway is:

D. Thymic stromal lymphocytes are created by TH2 cells which have detected the activation of the dendritic cell.

This fits into the flowchart as follows:
- Pathogen engulfed by O.C. cell which activates D.C. cell
- Activated D.C. cell secretes a hormone
- Thymic stromal lymphocytes are created by TH2 cells which have detected the activation of the dendritic cell
- TH2 cells promote IgE production, promote mast cell activity, and stimulate eosinophil production
- IgE binds to create Mast Cell IgE complexes
